# Page titles

Every route must set the browser `<title>` as:

```text
{page content} - {application name}
```

## Rules

- Use a **short hyphen** (`-`) only — never em dash (`—`) or en dash (`–`) in `<title>` tags
- Application name = `data.site.appName` (from `PUBLIC_APP_NAME` env via root layout)
- Use `formatPageTitle()` from `$lib/utils/page-title.ts` or `<PageTitle>` from `$lib/components/PageTitle.svelte` — do not hand-roll `<title>` strings in routes
- Admin pages: set the title in `AdminHeader.svelte` via its `title` prop (already wired)
- Error pages: use `src/routes/+error.svelte` with `PageTitle`

Em dashes in body copy and UI labels are fine; this rule applies to document `<title>` only.
